cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on robot manipulation tasks and uses reinforcement learning for experiments with a simulated robotic manipulator and stochastic trajectory optimization for experiments with a real robotic manipulator.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper uses visual activity features to encode the demonstration and mentions varying viewpoints of observation, object properties, scene background, and morphology of the manipulator.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the paper uses reinforcement learning for experiments with a simulated robotic manipulator.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a method for one-shot learning of robot manipulation tasks using observation learning.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with controlling a robotic manipulator to perform a task.
